</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,500,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1112,1138]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Remarks:</emphasis>
The present record is the seventh 
<taxonomicName box="[701,862,1112,1138]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis box="[701,774,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anoba</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[930,988,1112,1138]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">India</collectingCountry>
and first from any Indian island. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Swinhoe" baseAuthorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Anoba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rigida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anoba rigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is exclusively a Sundanian species preferring lowland open habitats in secondary, coastal and riverine forests with altitude ranging below 
<quantity box="[467,538,1184,1211]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[552,732,1184,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" refId="ref9467" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2005) The Moths of Borneo: Parts 15 &amp; 16; Family Noctuidae: Catocalinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 529 pp., 28 pls." type="book" year="2005">Holloway 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
